2. The grandson of Caesar’s sister, O. Octavius, was adopted by Caesar, and henceforth known as O. Icilius Caesar Octavianus. He was born 03 ss.c., formed the second triumvi- rate with Antony and Lepidus in 44; with Antony's help defeated Brutus and Cassius, the murderers of Caesar, in 42, at Philippi3 defeated Antony at Actium, in 31, and became sole master of the Roman world, which he ruled till his death in 14 A.D.
